article.headline: Dayton 49, Jacksonville 3
article.story: DAYTON, Ohio (AP) -- Kevin Hoyng passed for three touchdowns and ran for another and Joe Gulick rushed for two scores to lead Dayton past Jacksonville 49-3 on Saturday. Hoyng completed 15-of-22 passes for 290 yards without an interception. His touchdowns covered 9 yards to Nick Ruhe, 37 yards to Justin Watkins and 30 yards to J Michael Jonard. Hoyng also rushed for 42 yards on eight attempts, scoring on a 12-yard run for the Flyers (5-1, 1-1 Pioneer League). Gulick added touchdown runs of 5 and 17 yards, with Bob Balogun closing the scoring on a 21-yard run. The only points for the Dolphins (1-4, 0-2) came on Michael Zacco's 30-yard field goal early in the third quarter after the Flyers built a 35-0 halftime lead. Jonard had five catches for 119 yards for Dayton, which piled up 518 total yards while holding Jacksonville to 184. Quarterbacks Erik Stepelton, Chris Horton and Spencer Endsley combined to complete just 16-of-40 passes for 176 yards with one interception. The Flyers also had five sacks and limited the Dolphins to 8 rushing yards on 23 attempts.
